              <h5 class="card-title">OOP Task Management System</h5>
                <p class = "card-text">
                  <strong>Tech Stack: </strong>
                  Language: Python 3.x <br>
                  Paradigm: Object-Oriented Programming<br>
                  Core Concepts: Encapsulation, Object Collaboration, Class Design, Utility Methods<br>
                  Libraries Used: datetime(For managing deadlines and reminders) and Standard Python Built-Ins<br>
                </p>
                <p class="card-text">
                     The Smart OOP Study Planner is a Python console application that simulates a real-world study planner for students. 
                      It leverages object-oriented programming (OOP) principles to organize tasks, schedule study sessions, and track progress efficiently. <br><br>
                                      <strong>Highlights:</strong><br>
                          Encapsulation → Private attributes with safe getters/setters.

                          Object Collaboration → Updates in StudySession cascade through Task, Subject, and Student.

                          Core Classes → Student, Subject, Task, StudySession, Reminder, Planner.<br>

                            <strong>Key Features:</strong><br>
                          Add subjects and tasks with deadlines.

                          Mark tasks complete, detect overdue work.

                          Schedule, update, and cancel study sessions.

                          Generate reminders and prioritize tasks.

                          Produce simple schedules for all tasks.
                </p>

